{"TopicId":148890,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Changing back temperatures in Celsius ?","CreatedByName":"Francois424","CreatedById":98138,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T04:45:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Francois424","CreatedById":98138,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T04:45:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all, silly question...\u00A0 but in 1.0 (I think) Squad changed the temperatures in-game to Kelvin instead of previous Celsius.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any easy way for me to change it back?\u00A0\u00A0 It\u0027s not game breaking or anything... But it\u0027s just annoying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-29T04:51:13Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2016 04:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Francois424\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Archgeek","CreatedById":116048,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T04:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSubtract 273.16. \u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Francois424","CreatedById":98138,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T04:54:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222779039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148890\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475124791\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022116048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Archgeek\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Archgeek said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSubtract 273.16. \u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course... But I\u0027m lazy and I\u0027d prefer the game do it for me \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T09:29:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E installed, you can in-flight change the settings (flight data settings)\u00A0to metric etc. etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also change the Kelvin to Celcius.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, thats only when you like to play with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-29T09:29:41Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2016 09:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DrLicor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Francois424","CreatedById":98138,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T16:18:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222779247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148890\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475141357\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrLicor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, DrLicor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E installed, you can in-flight change the settings (flight data settings)\u00A0to metric etc. etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also change the Kelvin to Celcius.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, thats only when you like to play with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, dunno why your reply didn\u0027t ping like it usually does.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll probably be looking into far, if only to trim it and keep the celcius thing if the files exists to do so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a lead at least.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}